IMPORTANT Usage Notes for the package:

* Changes from 2.0.x to 2.2.x

  Existing version 2.0 config files are MOSTLY compatible with 2.2, but WILL
  require at least one change: Several modules have changed name, so the
  LoadModule statements will need updating.  The easiest way to do this is to
  replace the existing LoadModule statements with the ones in
  /etc/apache2/original/httpd.conf.

  Apache 2.2 has a significantly redesigned default configuration: it has been
  greatly simplified by removing all but the most essential configuration
  settings.  A set of example configuration settings for more advanced
  features is present in the /etc/apache2/extra/ directory.  Furthermore, the
  naming scheme of the pristine default configuration files has changed:
  Instead of /etc/apache2/httpd-std.conf, there is now
  /etc/apache2/original/httpd.conf, and similarly for other files.

  
* cygserver dependency
  
  Apache 2 makes use of IPC functions which are supported on Cygwin via
  cygserver.  This means you MUST ensure both of the following are true,
  to make the server run:
    
    1) The CYGWIN environment variable must contain "server".

    2) The cygserver daemon must be running.
       Run the command "cygserver-config" for interactive setup.


* Distributed template files and their active versions
  
  The active document root and cgi-bin directories are:
    * /srv/www/htdocs
    * /srv/www/cgi-bin

  The distributed example versions of these are placed at:
    * /usr/share/apache2/htdocs
    * /usr/share/apache2/cgi-bin
  
  The examples are copied to the active location only if the active version
  is missing, so your local content will be unaffected by package upgrades,
  but you can check the location under /usr/share should you desire to refer
  to the templates.

  The situation for configuration files is similar:
    Active directory:   /etc/apache2
    Template directory: /etc/apache2/original

  The template directory is updated by package upgrades - you should diff it
  against your active configuration files from time to time, to see if there
  are any upstream changes you would like to adopt.


* "2" suffixation
  
  The executables installed by this package are suffixed with the
  character "2".  This is done to permit the parallel installation of
  Apache 1.3.x and Apache 2.x on the same machine.


* Installation as a Windows service

  Example cygrunsrv command line:

  $ cygrunsrv -I httpd2 -d "CYGWIN httpd2" -p /usr/sbin/httpd2 \
      -a "-DNO_DETACH" -y cygserver -e "CYGWIN=server" -s TERM -o


